# Takeaway

The key idea is to recursively search both the left and right subtrees. If both recursive calls return non-null, the current node is the Lowest Common Ancestor. Otherwise, propagate the non-null result upward. This elegant **Search-and-Combine** recursion solves the problem in **O(n)** time and is one of the most frequently asked Binary Tree interview patterns.
